cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.AI, cs.IR 

The paper focuses on deep convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for person re-identification (ReID), which is a computer vision task related to image classification and object recognition. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the optimization and network improvements of CNNs, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper introduces a new dataset for comparing within-camera and across-camera person ReID, which could be categorized under cs.MM (Multimedia). The paper also mentions unsupervised domain adaptation techniques, which could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper evaluates the influence of training data and baseline network architecture, which could be categorized under cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
